S. in answer to yd of 26:t past. as to the cloversaid, though the bavrell was not
Bull, yett Ihope there is not vere much un beasuled, that you finde the weighe
to aggree, I have not yett the charges att gant butt expect itt dayly rith them
on the pictures which are peeces rolled up in alitte square cas & the fvannes
made up also in abundele, have don canvas about atyee the 2 parcells toghetter

for the case
ƒ 65:18 fis which I have payd ono
ƒ63:10 & made you Deb. accordingly, they must be att bruges by this time & hope when
they arrive will give you content, any the least that understands makeing of
fraines will cnsely putt them up in order, & have don itt so to make the parcell
the lesser as for the tykes Iassine you Inever sended yett one peece to Englend for
my acctt nather one peece yett in beurter & I should not have sent thise forwind
neither if itt had not been that with alt tb. last & was to ballance mj bocks
o& that feared any frost to provent their forwardness I should have kept them
here butt whilst they be att bruges have ordered mr. coots to ship theem off
for you they beeng not yett shipped I should be vere hard for mee to loose
so much lp on them eso I hope you will allow mee some thing towards
the chardges otherwise I can not send any more att that rats which pray
considder Ill according to yd or derdraw on you att as hight arate as possiblelen

London Henry Collier
S. my last to you was on the 3: curitt: sence have recd. yd cy past. by which I ronder
att yd proceeding what can itt discharge mee that you or mr. Knightley draws
if itt be for yd acctt & that I must accept itt where by every one must see
att what trade wee rin intrest either cor him Ideall with truelly
goods you knowitt vere well thatt t should not go so the bussynes metiond
in my least concerning my good freind n EW. do keep mee so imploged
that sence &didalmost not ing elce the more because wee ure upon recovang
part off itt that is the reason & have not yett drawne out yd accnt intrim
if you are not discoursed by Es. first, please to keep sec rett what I cont
yon & shall the sooner des puck yd acctt. that I mught have the konow
sae y some, orrother you the for if you should qultion my kindness toyon
ra ffue you that my father would be the greater & so wee might
